                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250519-194-off1112 t18250519-194-crimeloc1114"></join>. The prisoner was my <rs id="t18250519-194-deflabel1115" type="occupation">porter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250519-194-defend984 t18250519-194-deflabel1115"></join> for about fourteen months - he had 1 l. a week; he left me on Wednesday, the 6th of April - his week ended on Saturday; he was entrusted to receive money on my account, and when he returned home from any journey it was his business to account to one of my shopmen for the money he might have received. He took goods to Mary Backhouse the day before he left, and never accounted to me for any money he had received from her; he was apprehended in about five days.</p>
